title.narrative: EFFECTIVE MANAGEMENT AND DELIVERY OF INTEGRATED SOCIAL PROTECTION SERVICES

description.narrative: Social Protection service providers effectively manage and deliver integrated services that are adjusted to the specific needs of the poorest children., which contributes to Access To Inclusive Social Protection, Reducing Child Poverty. UNICEF aims to achieve this through Community Engagement, Social And Behaviour Change, Data, Research, Evaluation And Knowledge Management, Evaluations, Research And Data, Systems Strengthening And Institution Building, Systems Strengthening To Leave No One Behind. This contributes to the following Country Programme result: By 2023 the poorest children in Rwanda benefit from a strengthened and adequately-resourced integrated social protection system

description.narrative: UNICEF continues to support the government to undertake transformations in the social protection sector to ensure graduation from and eradication of extreme poverty. Important steps have been taken towards the delivery of Cash Plus programmes for households with children under five years of age. The nutrition-sensitive social protection pilots have shown some great successes which have been presented to the social protection SWG. Community-level activities of the JP being implemented in partnership with World Relief will further contribute to shaping Rwanda’s programming for integrated social protection interventions that support livelihoods enhancement. | Status:On-track | As-of Date:31/12/2021
